      <bioghist encodinganalog="MARC 545">
         <head id="a2" altrender="biography">BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE </head>
         <p>Educator.</p>
         <p>Bertha Stoneman graduated from Cornell, Class of 1894, and received a Doctor of Science degree in botany in 1896. She joined the faculty of Huguenot College in Wellington, Cape Colony (South Africa), a women's college. From 1928 until her retirement in 1933, she served as president of the college.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520">
         <head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
         <p>Correspondence, speeches, student notebooks, thesis, photographs, and poetry of Bertha Stoneman. Also, Huguenot College yearbooks, University of Toronto centenary programs (with a reference to Livingston Farrand), and pamphlets about South Africa.</p>
      </scopecontent>
